chat_messages.text:
 ## Absolutely Right - Text Service Architecture

Yes! I was mixing concerns. Let me correct that:

### Text Service Handles Exit Descriptions

```typescript
// In text service, not in behaviors
class TextService {
  describeExits(roomId: string): string {
    // Query for exits from this room
    const exits = this.world.find({
      type: 'exit',
      where: e => {
        const exit = e.get(TraitType.EXIT);
        return exit?.from === roomId && exit.listed;
      }
    });

    // Template and format the exit description
    return this.template('room.exits', { exits });
  }

  describeRoom(roomId: string): string {
    const room = this.world.get(roomId);
    const parts = [
      this.getDescription(room),
      this.describeExits(roomId),
      this.describeVisibleItems(roomId)
    ];

    return parts.filter(Boolean).join('\n\n');
  }
}
```

### Behaviors Just Return Semantic Events

```typescript
// RoomBehavior doesn't generate text
class RoomBehavior {
  static enter(actor: IFEntity, room: IFEntity): Event[] {
    // Just semantic events, no text
    return [
      createEvent(IFEvents.ACTOR_ENTERED, { 
        actor: actor.id, 
        room: room.id 
      })
    ];
  }
}
```

### Text Service Queries Build Descriptions

```typescript
// Text service owns all the complex description logic
class TextService {
  private getExitQueries() {
    return {
      // All visible exits from a room
      visibleExits: (roomId: string) => ({
        type: 'exit',
        where: e => e.get(TraitType.EXIT)?.from === roomId && 
                    e.get(TraitType.EXIT)?.visible
      }),

      // Exits that should be listed in description
      listedExits: (roomId: string) => ({
        type: 'exit',
        where: e => e.get(TraitType.EXIT)?.from === roomId && 
                    e.get(TraitType.EXIT)?.listed
      }),

      // Blocked exits (closed doors, etc)
      blockedExits: (roomId: string) => ({
        type: 'exit',
        where: e => {
          const exit = e.get(TraitType.EXIT);
          return exit?.from === roomId &&
                 e.has(TraitType.OPENABLE) &&
                 !e.get(TraitType.OPENABLE)?.isOpen;
        }
      })
    };
  }
}
```

### Clean Separation

- **Behaviors**: Logic only, return events
- **Text Service**: All queries for description building
- **Templates**: Actual text generation

This keeps the architecture clean. Thanks for catching that!

